**3.4 The Algebraic Identity**

**Hypothesis (B) is algebraically identical to (A).** For all K2n:
dim(so(2n−1)/so(2n−2)) = 2n − 2 = \|V(K2n)\| − 2. The coset dimension
and the vertex-minus-doublet count are the same number for structural
reasons (so(n)/so(n−1) = Sn−1 has dimension n−1). Neither can be
distinguished by its numerical value.

